Freenet has some well thought security concepts which Zeronet misses completely. Like warning that one is leaving from cipher to clearnet. Hell, by this even the referer get's forwarded to the targetlink.
Also Zeronet has no build in encryption of local content.
Though i see Zeronets main concept is not encryption/security but censorship protection.
But even censorship protection feels hard to believe for me:
1. Admins of a site can dictate how much space a user can use.
2. A user can easily (be forced to) delete/edit his content.
